1. Generate keypair with ssh_keygen (set new name).
2. powershell will store the keys in the current directory.
3. cd to C:\Users\$User/.ssh
4. copy both keys (public and private)
5. ssh -i id_ed25519_vultr root@address
6. enter the password vultr set upon creation.
7. this presupposes that the public key was inserted during vultr server creation process.
